Attachment A — Use Restrictions

You agree not to use the Model or its Derivatives in any of the following ways:

1. Legal

(a) In any way that violates any applicable national, federal, state, local or
international law or regulation.

2. Harm and Discrimination

(a) For the purpose of exploiting, harming or attempting to exploit or harm minors
in any way.

(b) To generate or disseminate false information with the purpose of harming
others.

(c) To generate or disseminate personal identifiable information that can be used
to harm an individual.

(d) To defame, disparage or otherwise harass others.

(e) For any use intended to or which has the effect of harming individuals or
groups based on online or offline social behavior or known or predicted personal
or personality characteristics.

(f) To exploit any of the vulnerabilities of a specific group of persons based on
their age, social, physical or mental characteristics, in order to materially
distort the behavior of a person belonging to that group in a manner that causes
or is likely to cause that person or another person harm.

(g) For any use intended to or which has the effect of discriminating against
individuals or groups based on legally protected characteristics or categories.

3. Transparency

(a) To generate or disseminate machine-generated information or content in any
medium without expressly and intelligibly disclaiming that it is machine-generated.

(b) To impersonate or attempt to impersonate human beings for purposes of
deception.

(c) For fully automated decision making that adversely impacts an individual's
legal rights or otherwise creates or modifies a binding, enforceable obligation.

4. Surveillance and Control (added by Licensor)

(a) For use in any surveillance system, mass monitoring infrastructure, or
technology whose primary purpose is tracking individuals without their explicit
consent.

(b) For use in any military, weapons, or lethal autonomous systems application.

(c) For use by law enforcement or government agencies for predictive policing,
criminal profiling, or immigration enforcement.

5. Centralization and Proprietary Capture (added by Licensor)

(a) For integration into a closed, proprietary commercial product or service where
the model weights, architecture improvements, or derivative training runs are not
made publicly available under equivalent open terms. If You build on this Model
commercially, You must contribute improvements back to the community under a
compatible open license.

(b) For use by any entity with annual AI-related revenue exceeding €10 million EUR
without explicit written permission from the Licensor. This restriction is intended
to prevent large-scale proprietary capture of community research while preserving
access for individuals, researchers, small organizations, and community projects.

6. Sovereign Computing Intent (added by Licensor)

The Licensor releases this Model in the spirit of democratizing AI access —
enabling individuals and communities to run, train, and improve language models
on hardware they own and control. Any use of this Model that undermines that
purpose, concentrates AI capability in centralized infrastructure, or weaponizes
it against the communities it was built to serve, is contrary to the intent of
this License and prohibited under paragraph 5 above.
